{"id":2375,"date":"2023-02-25T04:18:18","date_gmt":"2023-02-25T04:18:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/blog\/?p=2375"},"modified":"2023-03-20T19:42:00","modified_gmt":"2023-03-20T19:42:00","slug":"best-ides-for-python","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/blog\/best-ides-for-python\/","title":{"rendered":"BEST IDEs for Python"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Python is one of the most popular programming languages, used to build websites, games ,&nbsp; models in artificial intelligence and data analysis. It is a versatile language, with a strong emphasis on readability and simplicity which makes it easy to learn.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>After enrolling in a bootcamp or picking up a course, you have to practice what is taught to be familiar with the code syntaxes. We make use of IDEs and code editors to execute code blocks. An IDE ( Integrated Development Environment ) is a software tool that allows the user to&nbsp; run programming languages on it\u2019s platform, they have debuggers , built in extensions to make work efficient.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Features&nbsp; of an IDE<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Shortcut commands<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Syntax highlighting<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Autocomplete<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Indentation<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Debuggers<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Extensions&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Code editor are interfaces to write code that are usually run by a compiler or interpreter.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are IDEs that run online and some you have to install the application.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">IDE Applications<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.jetbrains.com\/pycharm\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Pycharm<\/a> <\/strong>: This IDE is very popular and it is developed by Jetbrains. It is very easy to use and navigate with python. You can also push your code from the pycharm terminal to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/blog\/what-is-github\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"2607\">github<\/a>. There is a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.jetbrains.com\/pycharm\/download\/#section=windows\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">community version of pycharm<\/a> that is free for everyone but the professional version is paid. As a student it is free all you need to do is to sign up for github <a href=\"https:\/\/education.github.com\/pack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">student developer pack<\/a> with your school email, answer a few questions then you get the license that gives you access to all the features. It has unique features like auto completion, debugging, code analysis showing previous changes and new changes, refactoring and\u00a0 automatic indentation of code blocks.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Pycharm-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"Pycharm\" class=\"wp-image-2376\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Pycharm-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Pycharm-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Pycharm.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.python.org\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Python IDLE<\/a>:<\/strong> IDLE means Integrated Development Learning Environment. It is beginner friendly in terms of navigation around the code environment and it\u2019s default language is python. It is compatible for windows and mac users. You need to install the python extension on your to access IDLE. Once installed, you search IDLE on your computer , click on it and the interface pops up. The code runs on the same interface as you type it, you just press the \u201center key\u201d to see the results.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"394\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Python-IDLE-1024x394.jpg\" alt=\"Python IDLE\" class=\"wp-image-2377\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Python-IDLE-1024x394.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Python-IDLE-300x115.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Python-IDLE.jpg 1258w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Jupyter Notebook: <\/strong>this IDE works like a notebook, where you write and edit code.it can be used but on <a href=\"https:\/\/jupyter.org\/try-jupyter\/retro\/notebooks\/?path=notebooks\/Intro.ipynb\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">the web<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/jupyter.org\/install\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">the application<\/a> can be installed. You run the command on your command prompt to download it. With the web app version of the notebook, you can share your work with others. To create a new file , you select \u201cNew\u201d then notebook<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"492\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Jupyter-Notebook-1024x492.jpg\" alt=\"Jupyter Notebook\" class=\"wp-image-2378\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Jupyter-Notebook-1024x492.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Jupyter-Notebook-300x144.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Jupyter-Notebook.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then, it bring out this option, you click select, then the cell shows.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"517\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Phyton-Pyodide-1024x517.jpg\" alt=\"Phyton Pyodide\" class=\"wp-image-2379\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Phyton-Pyodide-1024x517.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Phyton-Pyodide-300x152.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Phyton-Pyodide.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To execute any code block, you have to click on the &lt;cell&gt; and the \u201cplay button\u201d.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"264\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Run-the-selected-cells-1024x264.jpg\" alt=\"Run the selected cells\" class=\"wp-image-2380\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Run-the-selected-cells-1024x264.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Run-the-selected-cells-300x77.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Run-the-selected-cells.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/replit.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">REPL IT<\/a> <\/strong>: An online IDE that requires you to create an account and then you can use it for free. You can work with files alongside your code and save them for future use . It has built in python packages that helps to execute code. You can also share links of your project with your friends, they can help with your errors. Also, it is easy to install other python packages&nbsp; and run because it is an online IDE.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/www.sololearn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/REPL-IT-1024x508.jpg\" alt=\"REPL IT\" class=\"wp